text:
="preserve">Carlos José Zambrano García-Raez (born 23 February 1969) is a Spanish politician. He is a member of the far-right Vox party. Since 2019, he has served as a member of the Congress of Deputies. Before joining Vox, he was member of the People's Party. He was born in San Fernando, Cádiz.
On 11 March 2020, during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic, it was made clear that Zambrano García-Raez had tested positive to COVID-19.
